    {
      "title": "Homophones, homonyms, homographs",
      "html": "<p><b>Homophones</b> — sound the same but differ in spelling and meaning: <i>their / there / they're; principal / principle; stationery / stationary; bare / bear; peace / piece</i>.</p>\n  <p><b>Homonyms</b> — same spelling <u>and</u> same sound but different meanings: <i>bank</i> (river / financial); <i>bark</i> (of a tree / of a dog); <i>fair</i> (just / market).</p>\n  <p><b>Homographs</b> — same spelling but different meaning and often different pronunciation: <i>lead</i> (metal, /led/) vs <i>lead</i> (to guide, /liːd/); <i>tear</i> (from the eye, /tɪə/) vs <i>tear</i> (to rip, /teə/); <i>row</i> (a line) vs <i>row</i> (a quarrel).</p>",
      "examples": [
        {
          "q": "Choose the right word: <i>The wound had a (bare / bear) minimum of bandage.</i>",
          "a": "<b>bare</b> = minimum; <i>bear</i> = the animal or 'to endure'."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Phrasal verbs, idioms and collocations",
      "html": "<p>A <b>phrasal verb</b> is a verb + particle whose meaning is often not obvious from its parts: <i>put off</i> (postpone), <i>give up</i> (quit), <i>look after</i> (care for), <i>break down</i> (stop functioning; cry).</p>\n  <p>An <b>idiom</b> is a fixed expression whose meaning is not literal: <i>kick the bucket</i> (die), <i>let the cat out of the bag</i> (reveal a secret), <i>burn the midnight oil</i> (work late), <i>a piece of cake</i> (very easy).</p>\n  <p>A <b>collocation</b> is a natural word partnership: <i>make a decision</i> (not 'do a decision'), <i>strong tea</i> (not 'powerful tea'), <i>heavy rain</i>, <i>catch a cold</i>.</p>",
      "examples": [
        {
          "q": "Give the meaning of <i>burn the midnight oil</i>.",
          "a": "To work or study late into the night."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Registers — Medicine, Science, ICT",
      "html": "<p><b>Medicine</b>: diagnosis, prognosis, symptom, prescription, dosage, antibiotic, epidemic, surgery, anaesthetic, quarantine, immunisation.</p>\n  <p><b>Science</b> (general): hypothesis, experiment, control, variable, molecule, compound, catalyst, momentum, evaporation, ecosystem.</p>\n  <p><b>ICT</b>: hardware, software, byte, browser, encryption, algorithm, database, malware, cloud, bandwidth, firewall, protocol.</p>",
      "examples": [
        {
          "q": "Which register does <i>algorithm, encryption, malware</i> belong to?",
          "a": "ICT / Computing."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
